1
00:00:52,210 --> 00:00:55,560
<i>[Hong Kong Exchange]</i>

2
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:12,700
<i>[Bao Dian Expert]</i>

3
00:01:12,704 --> 00:01:14,546
- One of those, please.
- One?

4
00:01:14,546 --> 00:01:17,210
- Alright, one.
- That one.

5
00:01:19,251 --> 00:01:20,630
- That's six dollars.
- Here you go.

6
00:01:20,630 --> 00:01:22,480
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

7
00:01:22,480 --> 00:01:24,244
Thank you.

8
00:01:27,610 --> 00:01:29,820
That's so good!

9
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:34,698
<i>After a stint in Shanghai, I've been in Hong Kong for six months.</i>

10
00:01:34,698 --> 00:01:42,168
<i>The huge residential development has finished, so I'm headed back to Tokyo.</i>

11
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:44,930
<i>[Goods Nanfutong]</i>

12
00:01:46,167 --> 00:01:48,377
Hey, young fellow.

13
00:01:48,377 --> 00:01:51,430
It's a very good buy. It's so beautiful.

14
00:01:51,430 --> 00:01:54,540
Very beautiful. Good, good, good.

15
00:01:54,540 --> 00:01:55,810
This beautiful.

16
00:01:55,810 --> 00:01:58,543
It's really cheap. Take a look.

17
00:01:58,543 --> 00:02:01,902
See? It says, "Forever Love".

18
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,540
- Forever love?
- Yeah.

19
00:02:05,543 --> 00:02:08,093
You need to buy it. Come inside.

20
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:11,219
Thank you so much, handsome.

21
00:02:11,219 --> 00:02:13,061
Thank you.

22
00:02:22,794 --> 00:02:26,293
Hey! Come back!

23
00:02:45,076 --> 00:02:47,302
Sorry to interrupt.

24
00:03:04,127 --> 00:03:06,193
Bring it on.

25
00:03:09,293 --> 00:03:11,193
It's going to break!

26
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,544
Thank you.

27
00:03:23,710 --> 00:03:25,410
<i>[Cheong Ming Antiques]</i>

28
00:03:32,585 --> 00:03:33,668
Are you okay?

29
00:03:33,668 --> 00:03:35,227
Thank you.

30
00:03:35,227 --> 00:03:38,602
Be careful. Bye-bye.

31
00:03:42,877 --> 00:03:46,494
You dropped your key holder!

32
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,818
That was close!

33
00:04:19,835 --> 00:04:25,335
<i>It hasn't been long, but I've enjoyed working with you all.</i>

34
00:04:25,335 --> 00:04:28,044
<i>Do your best in Japan, Haruta.</i>

35
00:04:28,044 --> 00:04:33,260
<i>I shared great times, joys, and sorrows with my co-workers.</i>

36
00:04:35,127 --> 00:04:37,260
<i>Maybe I enjoyed too much.</i>

37
00:04:41,051 --> 00:04:43,826
<i>That's what I realized when I woke up the next morning.</i>

38
00:04:55,710 --> 00:04:57,510
What?

39
00:04:59,510 --> 00:05:03,620
<i>[Cofee | Snacks]</i>

40
00:05:05,919 --> 00:05:08,402
Hey, wake up.

41
00:05:23,626 --> 00:05:25,633
Hello.

42
00:05:25,633 --> 00:05:27,457
Maki?

43
00:05:28,835 --> 00:05:30,535
Maki.

44
00:05:30,535 --> 00:05:32,427
Why are you here?

45
00:05:34,668 --> 00:05:39,635
Maki!

46
00:05:40,254 --> 00:05:42,220
Who's the guy?

47
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:43,854
What?

48
00:05:48,836 --> 00:05:51,654
You've got it all wrong.

49
00:05:51,654 --> 00:05:53,695
I don't know him at all.

50
00:05:53,695 --> 00:05:56,054
Maki, why are you here in Hong Kong?

51
00:05:56,054 --> 00:05:57,970
Cut it out.

52
00:05:57,970 --> 00:06:00,129
No, wait!

53
00:06:00,129 --> 00:06:01,862
Don't go!

54
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:05,478
No, don't go!

55
00:06:05,478 --> 00:06:07,130
I've seen enough. Bye.

56
00:06:07,130 --> 00:06:09,513
Maki! Maki!

57
00:06:15,386 --> 00:06:17,069
Coffee or tea?

58
00:06:17,927 --> 00:06:20,703
Go home!

59
00:06:21,261 --> 00:06:28,494
<i>My God, what became of the eternal love I swore to him?</i>

60
00:06:41,827 --> 00:06:44,212
<i>Soichi Haruta, 33 years old. I want to fall in love!</i>

61
00:06:44,212 --> 00:06:47,004
<i>I adore you, Haru-tan!</i>

62
00:06:47,004 --> 00:06:51,663
<i>- I'm like you.
- Can you please stop fighting over me!</i>

63
00:06:57,711 --> 00:07:00,154
<i>You can love whoever you want.</i>

64
00:07:00,154 --> 00:07:01,887
<i>- I want a divorce.
- Another woman?</i>

65
00:07:01,887 --> 00:07:04,670
<i>- He's my ex-lover.
- I can't live without him.</i>

66
00:07:04,670 --> 00:07:07,113
<i>I love you, Haruta.</i>

67
00:07:11,295 --> 00:07:13,795
<i>I was so happy to meet you.</i>

68
00:07:13,795 --> 00:07:15,712
<i>I don't love you, anymore.</i>

69
00:07:15,712 --> 00:07:18,378
<i>Haruta, go!</i>

70
00:07:18,378 --> 00:07:22,320
<i>Please marry me!</i>

71
00:07:30,537 --> 00:07:36,430
<i>[Ossan's Love, The Movie - LOVE or DEAD]</i>

72
00:07:37,012 --> 00:07:40,712
Finally! Feels good to be back!

73
00:07:47,186 --> 00:07:49,296
Wow, I'm sorry.

74
00:07:49,296 --> 00:07:51,803
Please excuse me.

75
00:07:51,803 --> 00:07:53,837
It's fine. I'll do it myself.

76
00:07:53,837 --> 00:07:56,778
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

77
00:08:06,129 --> 00:08:08,920
Here you go.

78
00:08:12,962 --> 00:08:15,479
- Thanks.
- Pretty.

79
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:18,630
Thanks.

80
00:08:19,810 --> 00:08:22,190
Ouch!

81
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:26,890
I think I heard something break.

82
00:08:26,890 --> 00:08:29,500
<i>[Tenku Real Estate Co. Ltda.]</i>

83
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:31,604
I'm back!

84
00:08:31,604 --> 00:08:33,379
Welcome back!

85
00:08:33,379 --> 00:08:35,229
Haruta-san!

86
00:08:36,128 --> 00:08:38,087
Welcome back, Haruta.

87
00:08:38,087 --> 00:08:39,112
Finally home.

88
00:08:39,112 --> 00:08:41,062
Good work.

89
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:42,571
You could have taken the day off.

90
00:08:42,571 --> 00:08:45,671
- Do my work if you don't want a rest.
- Shut up.

91
00:09:10,795 --> 00:09:13,352
Well done for the past year, Haruta.

92
00:09:13,352 --> 00:09:19,069
Director! I, Soichi Haruta, have completed my mission and I'm safely back from Hong Kong.

93
00:09:19,069 --> 00:09:21,300
Welcome back!

94
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:23,640
Welcome back!

95
00:09:29,505 --> 00:09:31,963
Good, I want you to meet someone.

96
00:09:31,963 --> 00:09:34,163
Come here.

97
00:09:36,379 --> 00:09:38,446
You are the one just now—

98
00:09:38,446 --> 00:09:41,946
This is Yamada, who just joined us this month.

99
00:09:43,505 --> 00:09:45,863
"Masayoshi Yamada?"

100
00:09:45,863 --> 00:09:48,588
No, not Masayoshi.

101
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:50,497
- Justice.
- Justice?

102
00:09:50,497 --> 00:09:53,921
Please call me Justice.

103
00:09:53,921 --> 00:09:55,870
That's too close!

104
00:09:55,870 --> 00:09:58,750
Justice!

105
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:02,088
Haruta, please take care of me at work.

106
00:10:03,372 --> 00:10:06,164
You can count on me.

107
00:10:08,005 --> 00:10:10,506
Excuse me, but where's Maki?

108
00:10:10,506 --> 00:10:13,506
Maki?

109
00:10:19,855 --> 00:10:22,372
What's going on?

110
00:10:33,297 --> 00:10:36,380
Good morning, people from the Sales Department.

111
00:10:36,380 --> 00:10:37,629
Good morning.

112
00:10:37,629 --> 00:10:40,946
- I'm Mamiana, from the Development Division.
- Who is he?

113
00:10:40,946 --> 00:10:43,364
Is he from the head office?

114
00:10:43,364 --> 00:10:47,855
Regarding the ongoing Tokyo Bay Laputa Project,

115
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:51,304
the head office will take control of all the related information.

116
00:10:51,304 --> 00:10:57,003
Therefore, I must ask you all to please vacate this area immediately.

117
00:10:57,003 --> 00:11:00,513
Wait up. What is this about, Director?

118
00:11:00,513 --> 00:11:03,188
Director Kurosawa. It's been a while.

119
00:11:03,188 --> 00:11:05,213
Listen, Mamiana.

120
00:11:05,213 --> 00:11:09,297
It's a problem for us to leave with such short notice.

121
00:11:09,297 --> 00:11:11,105
Exactly. What are you trying to do?

122
00:11:11,105 --> 00:11:13,121
We have ongoing work here.

123
00:11:13,121 --> 00:11:15,921
There will be an official announcement next week.

124
00:11:15,921 --> 00:11:20,963
And we intend to involve you all in part of the project.

125
00:11:20,963 --> 00:11:26,681
Please make use of your excess energy to do things then.

126
00:11:26,681 --> 00:11:27,739
What excess energy?

127
00:11:27,739 --> 00:11:31,381
Of course, we'll assist you wherever we can.

128
00:11:31,381 --> 00:11:33,839
But isn't this a bit too sudden?

129
00:11:33,839 --> 00:11:35,914
Sorry to keep you waiting.

130
00:11:42,672 --> 00:11:44,756
Maki, come here.

131
00:11:44,756 --> 00:11:46,507
Everything's ready.

132
00:11:46,507 --> 00:11:48,391
Good work.

133
00:11:48,391 --> 00:11:51,423
Haruta, Maki got transferred to head office last week.

134
00:11:51,423 --> 00:11:53,948
What? Seriously?

135
00:11:53,948 --> 00:11:55,697
You two are married, didn't you know about it?

136
00:11:55,697 --> 00:11:59,206
Okay, we need to get work going.

137
00:11:59,206 --> 00:12:01,170
<i>Yes, Sir.</i>

138
00:12:03,048 --> 00:12:05,806
Pack everything away.

139
00:12:05,806 --> 00:12:07,973
What the hell is this?

140
00:12:09,448 --> 00:12:11,348
You can just leave that.

141
00:12:12,506 --> 00:12:16,006
Maki, what's going on? Fill me in.

142
00:12:16,006 --> 00:12:18,165
Please let him go.

143
00:12:26,573 --> 00:12:29,139
<i>[Drinking & Dining Pub Wonderful]</i>

144
00:12:29,797 --> 00:12:31,523
<i>[Teppei Arai in Concert]</i>

145
00:12:31,523 --> 00:12:34,156
What's with that guy anyway?

146
00:12:34,156 --> 00:12:36,082
He was so stand-offish.

147
00:12:36,082 --> 00:12:37,889
- Well...
- Ice-cold eyes.

148
00:12:37,889 --> 00:12:40,073
Don't get so bitchy about it.

149
00:12:40,073 --> 00:12:42,073
I wasn't being bitchy.

150
00:12:42,073 --> 00:12:45,256
Your half-and-half curry and chocolate.

151
00:12:45,256 --> 00:12:47,923
You got it wrong! I ordered chicken and egg on rice.

152
00:12:47,923 --> 00:12:50,214
Don't complain, just eat whatever you are served.

153
00:12:50,214 --> 00:12:51,733
- Get on with it.
- How annoying.

154
00:12:51,733 --> 00:12:54,032
Just go on and eat.

155
00:12:55,173 --> 00:12:57,764
- The restaurant looks great?
- Sure does.

156
00:13:01,506 --> 00:13:02,632
You need to try it.

157
00:13:02,632 --> 00:13:04,530
- No, thanks.
- Seriously.

158
00:13:06,389 --> 00:13:08,414
Not a chance.

159
00:13:08,423 --> 00:13:11,114
This is the most insane combination ever.

160
00:13:11,114 --> 00:13:13,365
- It tastes like shit.
- Don't say that.

161
00:13:13,365 --> 00:13:14,306
It's crap.

162
00:13:14,306 --> 00:13:18,173
I knew Maki was back at head office.

163
00:13:18,173 --> 00:13:20,048
Really? But why?

164
00:13:20,048 --> 00:13:23,923
What's happened over this year? He's totally changed.

165
00:13:23,923 --> 00:13:26,257
Only because you had an affair.

166
00:13:26,257 --> 00:13:28,324
No, I didn't.

167
00:13:28,324 --> 00:13:31,881
Did Maki tell you that?

168
00:13:32,965 --> 00:13:34,674
He got it all wrong.

169
00:13:34,674 --> 00:13:38,466
<i>He was dead-drunk, so I took him home, okay?</i>

170
00:13:38,466 --> 00:13:40,407
<i>Then I ended up sleeping beside him.</i>

171
00:13:40,407 --> 00:13:42,606
- You are guilty then.
- No! I'm totally innocent.

172
00:13:42,606 --> 00:13:46,231
Long-term relationships do have rough patches.

173
00:13:47,923 --> 00:13:51,523
So, are things going well for you and your boyfriend?

174
00:13:51,523 --> 00:13:53,574
Boyfriend?

175
00:13:53,574 --> 00:13:56,224
That handsome butler guy.

176
00:13:58,658 --> 00:14:03,123
What? Don't give me that scary face!

177
00:14:03,123 --> 00:14:04,823
You two broke up?

178
00:14:04,823 --> 00:14:10,507
Well, we have such different backgrounds, and our tastes and values were miles apart.

179
00:14:10,507 --> 00:14:15,132
We thought about our future, then decided to part.

180
00:14:15,132 --> 00:14:17,549
Some guy finally broke Chizu's heart!

181
00:14:17,549 --> 00:14:20,257
- I dumped him!
- Cheers!

182
00:14:20,257 --> 00:14:22,549
I was the one who dumped him!

183
00:14:22,549 --> 00:14:24,240
- Cheers!
- He was the one being dumped!

184
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:25,325
You'll find a better one next time.

185
00:14:25,325 --> 00:14:29,841
Maki! I'm back.

186
00:14:29,841 --> 00:14:31,132
You're drunk.

187
00:14:31,132 --> 00:14:33,632
- Not at all.
- Yes, you are.

188
00:14:33,632 --> 00:14:35,467
No, I'm not drunk.

189
00:14:35,467 --> 00:14:37,600
What's wrong with you?

190
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:43,616
What?

191
00:14:44,758 --> 00:14:49,891
Why didn't you mention your transfer to the head office?

192
00:14:49,891 --> 00:14:52,958
What's the reason? Tell me.

193
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:57,336
That's why I went to Hong Kong to tell you.

194
00:14:57,336 --> 00:14:59,919
But I decided not to say it.

195
00:14:59,919 --> 00:15:04,175
No, you got that wrong. I don't know that guy at all.

196
00:15:04,175 --> 00:15:07,359
Okay. I don't care, anyway.

197
00:15:07,359 --> 00:15:10,049
Then why are you in a bad mood?

198
00:15:10,049 --> 00:15:13,424
Especially when I'm back, after a year apart.

199
00:15:13,424 --> 00:15:15,391
I'm not angry.

200
00:15:16,716 --> 00:15:18,866
I'm just tired. You've eaten, haven't you?

201
00:15:18,866 --> 00:15:21,300
No. I'll eat it.

202
00:15:30,060 --> 00:15:32,530
<i>[Tenku Real Estate Co. Ltda.]</i>

203
00:15:35,150 --> 00:15:37,090
<i>[Genius 7]</i>

204
00:15:38,507 --> 00:15:41,049
- Ge-ni-us?
- It's Genius 7.

205
00:15:41,049 --> 00:15:43,466
It's Chairman Hayami's latest pet project.

206
00:15:43,466 --> 00:15:44,549
So what?

207
00:15:44,549 --> 00:15:50,849
Next, I would like to introduce the team that will lead the Tokyo Bay Laputa Project.

208
00:15:50,849 --> 00:15:55,352
Genius 7 Team, please come up to the stage.

209
00:16:09,716 --> 00:16:13,340
They're the guys who raided our office.

210
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:16,840
That's the Genius 7 Team?

211
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:19,499
And why is Maki with them?

212
00:16:19,499 --> 00:16:25,800
Our project will build one of Japan's biggest resorts in the Tokyo Bay area

213
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:29,800
using sites available after the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.

214
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:35,825
This is in partnership with the Phoenix Mountain Resort Group.

215
00:16:35,825 --> 00:16:39,770
And together, we have formed the invincible Genius 7 Team.

216
00:16:39,770 --> 00:16:41,350
<i>[Genius 7]</i>

217
00:16:44,966 --> 00:16:49,175
It has been my dream since I first started work here,

218
00:16:49,175 --> 00:16:56,108
to build a town loved by all, a community of a million smiles.

219
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:03,508
It's like he's from a different planet.

220
00:17:03,508 --> 00:17:07,133
Don't forget that Maki is always an elite.

221
00:17:07,675 --> 00:17:11,966
He only worked with us to gain practical experience.

222
00:17:11,966 --> 00:17:16,316
Did he ever mention this long-held dream to you?

223
00:17:16,316 --> 00:17:17,941
Never.

224
00:17:21,508 --> 00:17:27,865
The Sales team must secure all the land we need to accomplish our goals,

225
00:17:27,865 --> 00:17:31,065
by the end of the month.

226
00:17:31,065 --> 00:17:33,358
That's too big an area. It's impossible.

227
00:17:33,358 --> 00:17:34,785
By the end of the month? Ridiculous.

228
00:17:34,785 --> 00:17:38,551
In closing, our Chairman shall say a few words.

229
00:17:39,393 --> 00:17:42,343
All for Genius!

230
00:17:42,343 --> 00:17:44,717
<i>All for Genius!</i>

231
00:17:44,717 --> 00:17:47,364
Genius for all!
<i>[Chairman Reijiro Hayami]</i>

232
00:17:47,364 --> 00:17:50,179
<i>Genius for all!</i>

233
00:18:09,717 --> 00:18:13,383
Will you accept our offer to relocate?

234
00:18:13,383 --> 00:18:16,925
No way. All our customers are locals.

235
00:18:16,925 --> 00:18:19,383
I couldn't agree more.

236
00:18:19,383 --> 00:18:21,126
- Thank you, anyway.
- Thank you.

237
00:18:21,126 --> 00:18:24,077
About buying your business...

238
00:18:24,077 --> 00:18:28,534
How about if we slip you an extra 5 big ones?

239
00:18:29,801 --> 00:18:32,093
- This is the latest...
- I've said no countless times.

240
00:18:32,093 --> 00:18:33,418
Can I just leave the materials with you?

241
00:18:33,418 --> 00:18:38,093
We're building a city with a million smiles with the Tokyo Laputa Resort. Please have a look.

242
00:18:38,093 --> 00:18:40,743
It's the newest Tokyo Laputa resort.

243
00:18:40,743 --> 00:18:43,076
Please. I insist.

244
00:18:47,885 --> 00:18:52,718
They've lived there for generations, so they'll never sell their land.

245
00:18:52,718 --> 00:18:55,259
I couldn't agree more. I also think so.

246
00:18:55,259 --> 00:18:56,368
It's obvious.

247
00:18:56,368 --> 00:19:01,468
And besides, what's with that Mamiana guy?

248
00:19:01,468 --> 00:19:03,801
I just don't like him.

249
00:19:03,801 --> 00:19:07,017
Me, neither. I dislike the way he looks down on people.

250
00:19:07,017 --> 00:19:09,959
Yes, I agree.

251
00:19:09,959 --> 00:19:12,576
Agree.

252
00:19:13,493 --> 00:19:16,968
You know, I feel like we've known each other for a long time.

253
00:19:16,968 --> 00:19:18,668
Same here.

254
00:19:20,885 --> 00:19:24,301
By the way, what sports did you do in high school?

255
00:19:24,301 --> 00:19:25,676
Basketball.

256
00:19:25,676 --> 00:19:27,926
Me, too. What position?

257
00:19:27,926 --> 00:19:29,134
Point guard.

258
00:19:29,134 --> 00:19:30,718
Me too!

259
00:19:30,718 --> 00:19:32,260
But...

260
00:19:32,968 --> 00:19:36,060
We were both substitutes!

261
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:37,843
<i>[Udon Noodles Goro (Hand-Made)]</i>

262
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,217
Anybody inside?

263
00:19:39,217 --> 00:19:41,468
Excuse me.

264
00:19:41,468 --> 00:19:42,968
We're still preparing.

265
00:19:42,968 --> 00:19:44,968
Sorry to interrupt your work.

266
00:19:44,968 --> 00:19:46,811
I'm Haruta from Tenku Real Estate.

267
00:19:46,811 --> 00:19:49,077
No, thanks. Bugger off.

268
00:19:49,077 --> 00:19:52,743
Actually, a major new shopping center will be built in this area...

269
00:19:52,743 --> 00:19:55,084
Get out now!

270
00:19:59,885 --> 00:20:02,259
Excuse me. We'll take our leave.

271
00:20:02,801 --> 00:20:06,001
Please excuse us.

272
00:20:15,301 --> 00:20:20,618
We have no choice but to come again to make him listen.

273
00:20:22,468 --> 00:20:24,634
Thank you.

274
00:20:24,634 --> 00:20:26,093
For what?

275
00:20:26,093 --> 00:20:30,034
Just now, you saved me from falling.

276
00:20:33,384 --> 00:20:36,618
Haruta, you're like a big brother to me.

277
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,360
Big brother?

278
00:20:46,827 --> 00:20:48,627
Let's go.

279
00:20:55,010 --> 00:20:58,309
<i>Most slammed the doors in our faces.</i>

280
00:20:58,309 --> 00:21:00,761
<i>It's not the money they want.</i>

281
00:21:00,761 --> 00:21:04,139
<i>What about dinner? Will you be late?</i>

282
00:21:04,139 --> 00:21:06,768
<i>I'm making fried chicken.</i>

283
00:21:07,593 --> 00:21:09,552
<i>When will you be home?</i>

284
00:21:09,552 --> 00:21:11,577
<i>Are you there?</i>

285
00:21:12,426 --> 00:21:14,451
Thank you for the food.

286
00:21:23,968 --> 00:21:25,810
I'm home.

287
00:21:30,593 --> 00:21:32,593
It's burnt.

288
00:21:44,259 --> 00:21:46,751
Why am I not surprised?

289
00:21:58,886 --> 00:22:00,786
You're back.

290
00:22:00,786 --> 00:22:02,302
Hi, there.

291
00:22:02,302 --> 00:22:03,552
Listen, Maki.

292
00:22:03,552 --> 00:22:07,594
I know you're busy, but you should at least reply to my texts.

293
00:22:07,594 --> 00:22:08,595
Sorry.

294
00:22:08,595 --> 00:22:12,087
I busted my ass making dinner.

295
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:17,719
I mean, if we ever do decide to get married,

296
00:22:17,719 --> 00:22:23,027
we need to talk and cooperate with each other, right?

297
00:22:26,359 --> 00:22:29,159
Are you serious about marriage?

298
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:31,260
What?

299
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:32,960
No, it's nothing.

300
00:22:32,960 --> 00:22:34,844
No, don't say that...

301
00:22:34,844 --> 00:22:38,760
Did you think I was joking when I asked you to marry me?

302
00:22:38,760 --> 00:22:41,502
I didn't think that way.

303
00:22:41,502 --> 00:22:45,310
But there's no need to rush things.

304
00:22:46,052 --> 00:22:48,694
I'm not rushing things.

305
00:23:00,552 --> 00:23:01,844
Mom?

306
00:23:01,844 --> 00:23:03,719
Why are you here suddenly?

307
00:23:03,719 --> 00:23:06,385
Sorry to inform you at the last minute,

308
00:23:06,385 --> 00:23:08,777
but Ataru and I are moving in here.

309
00:23:08,777 --> 00:23:11,927
What! Who's Ataru, anyway?

310
00:23:11,927 --> 00:23:14,011
Let's see. Where did I leave my bankbook?

311
00:23:14,011 --> 00:23:17,127
Is this guy scamming you, Mom?

312
00:23:17,127 --> 00:23:19,677
- Hello.
- Long time no see.

313
00:23:19,677 --> 00:23:23,435
That's right. I forgot you live with a friend.

314
00:23:24,343 --> 00:23:26,719
I've been meaning to tell you.

315
00:23:26,719 --> 00:23:29,385
- Actually, Maki and I are...
- No problem.

316
00:23:29,385 --> 00:23:31,919
I'm also thinking of moving back to my parents'.

317
00:23:32,635 --> 00:23:35,886
It's closer to the head office. I can move immediately.

318
00:23:35,886 --> 00:23:39,352
I see. Are you sure it's not a problem?

319
00:23:40,419 --> 00:23:41,927
It's fine.

320
00:23:41,927 --> 00:23:44,552
- No, it's not.
- It is.

321
00:23:45,382 --> 00:23:46,272
See you.

322
00:23:46,272 --> 00:23:48,444
<i>A couple of days later,</i>

323
00:23:48,444 --> 00:23:53,245
<i>Maki packed his stuff and moved back home.</i>

324
00:23:56,651 --> 00:24:01,136
Our sales team has worked hard on the buyout negotiations.

325
00:24:01,136 --> 00:24:05,669
But we still need more time.

326
00:24:05,669 --> 00:24:11,678
Sorry, Director Kurosawa, but there's no time to waste.

327
00:24:11,678 --> 00:24:17,760
The Bay area is a historical township, with many old, established businesses.

328
00:24:17,760 --> 00:24:24,106
It takes multiple visits to build trust and convince them to sell.

329
00:24:24,106 --> 00:24:30,595
If you can't meet the company's expectations, then quit the project.

330
00:24:30,595 --> 00:24:36,137
I trusted you to lead your team properly, Director Kurosawa.

331
00:24:36,845 --> 00:24:38,612
Listen properly.

332
00:24:39,346 --> 00:24:42,570
I never said we can't do it.

333
00:24:44,470 --> 00:24:46,237
Please.

334
00:24:47,012 --> 00:24:50,079
Hurry up.

335
00:24:53,223 --> 00:25:00,278
Yes, I do.

336
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:10,370
We'll talk once you receive the data I've sent.

337
00:25:22,900 --> 00:25:24,960
<i>[Ganryu Second Hospital]</i>

338
00:25:32,472 --> 00:25:34,496
Over here, Choko-san.

339
00:25:36,721 --> 00:25:38,096
It's been a while.

340
00:25:38,096 --> 00:25:40,571
Yes, indeed.

341
00:25:41,263 --> 00:25:43,180
Is he all right?

342
00:25:43,180 --> 00:25:46,496
The doctor is in there with him now. We are waiting outside.

343
00:25:46,496 --> 00:25:50,346
Excuse me. Are you Mr. Kurosawa's family?

344
00:25:50,346 --> 00:25:51,946
<i>Yes!</i>

345
00:25:51,946 --> 00:25:53,637
- This way, please.
- Is he okay?

346
00:25:53,637 --> 00:25:55,130
- Please follow me.
- Is he conscious?

347
00:25:55,130 --> 00:25:57,910
- You need help?
- I'm okay.

348
00:25:58,928 --> 00:26:02,721
He's passed all the tests, but he needs rest for a few days.

349
00:26:02,721 --> 00:26:07,288
He's not in a coma, is he?

350
00:26:07,288 --> 00:26:09,538
He's just sleeping now. Don't worry.

351
00:26:09,538 --> 00:26:11,797
Can you guarantee he is all right?

352
00:26:11,797 --> 00:26:14,763
Don't worry. He won't die.

353
00:26:14,763 --> 00:26:18,063
- But still, Mrs. Kurosawa...
- No, no, no. She is Ex-Mrs. Kurosawa.

354
00:26:18,063 --> 00:26:20,280
Now she's my girlfriend.

355
00:26:21,513 --> 00:26:24,170
- Director.
- What?

356
00:26:31,750 --> 00:26:36,220
<i>[Live]</i>

357
00:26:37,096 --> 00:26:41,721
The Director is in hospital, but Maki didn't even visit him!

358
00:26:41,721 --> 00:26:45,846
Plus, he moved out. Is work really that important to him?

359
00:26:45,846 --> 00:26:47,846
Don't be so petty.

360
00:26:47,846 --> 00:26:51,126
You're petty and narrow-minded.

361
00:26:51,126 --> 00:26:51,979
What?

362
00:26:51,979 --> 00:26:53,913
You're jealous. That's not cool at all.

363
00:26:53,913 --> 00:26:56,399
I'm not jealous.

364
00:26:56,399 --> 00:26:59,564
And don't say that. People might think lowly of me.

365
00:26:59,564 --> 00:27:01,038
- Anyway, you don't have a good reputation.
- Don't think that much!

366
00:27:01,038 --> 00:27:03,679
He means his own dignity.

367
00:27:03,679 --> 00:27:05,305
Hi there, Maki.

368
00:27:05,305 --> 00:27:07,704
Come sit down.

369
00:27:09,628 --> 00:27:11,679
How's the Director?

370
00:27:11,679 --> 00:27:15,013
It's not serious, but he was still asleep.

371
00:27:15,013 --> 00:27:16,972
That's a relief.

372
00:27:17,554 --> 00:27:19,754
Sorry I couldn't visit him.

373
00:27:23,221 --> 00:27:26,679
That Seven project thing is still keeping you busy?

374
00:27:26,679 --> 00:27:31,971
Yes, there's so much to do, I'm still catching up.

375
00:27:33,679 --> 00:27:39,054
Don't overdo it and fall sick. Then you'd lose everything.

376
00:27:40,970 --> 00:27:44,679
Surprisingly, I've never felt more vital, or more alive.

377
00:27:44,679 --> 00:27:46,096
I totally get that.

378
00:27:46,096 --> 00:27:50,596
I also need to work hard to start my own business before I'm 40.

379
00:27:50,596 --> 00:27:52,472
Set up your own business? Are you thinking of that?

380
00:27:52,472 --> 00:27:53,804
I'll drink to that.

381
00:27:53,804 --> 00:27:57,263
And you, Haruta? What do you want to achieve?

382
00:27:57,263 --> 00:28:00,054
Me? Achieve what?

383
00:28:00,054 --> 00:28:01,221
Listen, Haruta.

384
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:05,679
No matter how old you are, it's important to have dreams.

385
00:28:05,679 --> 00:28:08,096
Then, what's your dream?

386
00:28:08,096 --> 00:28:10,196
My dream is...

387
00:28:11,002 --> 00:28:13,013
to fill up the <i>Nippon Budokan</i>.
<i>(T/N: Japan Martial Arts Hall)</i>

388
00:28:13,013 --> 00:28:15,263
Get real. That's impossible.

389
00:28:15,263 --> 00:28:18,613
- Shut up! You don't even have a dream.
- There's a waiting list.

390
00:28:18,613 --> 00:28:20,380
- For what?
- For his fans.

391
00:28:20,380 --> 00:28:23,821
Waiting list? Are you going to sing now?

392
00:28:24,563 --> 00:28:26,930
I have to work harder.

393
00:28:26,930 --> 00:28:27,800
Yes.

394
00:28:27,804 --> 00:28:29,713
See my new watch?

395
00:28:29,713 --> 00:28:31,637
It looks so good.

396
00:28:31,637 --> 00:28:35,380
It's an investment.

397
00:28:35,380 --> 00:28:40,420
♪ <i>Even if the dream is violently destroyed</i> ♪

398
00:28:51,805 --> 00:28:53,905
Ah, look at this.

399
00:28:55,422 --> 00:28:58,375
<i>[Fireworks Festival July 20th, 7pm to 8pm]</i>
We said we would attend this year, remember?

400
00:28:59,097 --> 00:29:01,347
Yes, but aren't you too busy?

401
00:29:01,347 --> 00:29:04,247
I will make time for it. What about you?

402
00:29:04,247 --> 00:29:06,014
I'm definitely going.

403
00:29:06,014 --> 00:29:07,389
I bet you forgot.

404
00:29:07,389 --> 00:29:08,889
- No, I didn't.
- You did.

405
00:29:08,889 --> 00:29:10,164
I didn't forget.

406
00:29:10,164 --> 00:29:11,272
Okay, just forget it.

407
00:29:11,272 --> 00:29:13,930
Seriously? I really remembered.

408
00:29:13,930 --> 00:29:15,739
What's this about?

409
00:29:24,872 --> 00:29:27,014
Ouch! You're hurting me. What is it?

410
00:29:27,014 --> 00:29:29,689
There's a burdock in your hair.

411
00:29:31,472 --> 00:29:34,205
- How'd that get there?
- How would I know?

412
00:29:35,055 --> 00:29:37,489
Okay, now open wide.

413
00:29:39,805 --> 00:29:43,306
No, no! You shouldn't waste food.

414
00:29:43,306 --> 00:29:46,606
See? Good boy.

415
00:29:46,606 --> 00:29:48,889
How long was it there?

416
00:30:05,389 --> 00:30:06,989
See you.

417
00:30:06,989 --> 00:30:08,639
Okay.

418
00:30:41,264 --> 00:30:43,250
Haruta, we'll start with you.

419
00:30:43,250 --> 00:30:44,880
Yes, Sir!

420
00:30:47,056 --> 00:30:48,431
Morning.

421
00:30:48,431 --> 00:30:50,798
- Director?!
- Director!

422
00:30:50,798 --> 00:30:53,423
Sorry I'm late.

423
00:30:53,423 --> 00:30:56,248
We've been so worried.

424
00:30:56,248 --> 00:30:57,889
Shouldn't you be resting?

425
00:30:57,889 --> 00:31:01,281
I'm fine. Look, I'm full of beans.

426
00:31:01,281 --> 00:31:03,831
Well done, Sir.

427
00:31:05,723 --> 00:31:08,839
- Was it really just an accident?
- What?

428
00:31:09,640 --> 00:31:11,640
Or were you pushed by someone?

429
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:12,624
Don't be silly.

430
00:31:12,624 --> 00:31:14,748
I doubt that.

431
00:31:14,748 --> 00:31:19,125
Anyway, we're just pleased to know you weren't badly injured.

432
00:31:19,125 --> 00:31:21,359
That's good news.

433
00:31:24,925 --> 00:31:28,250
- What's your name?
- Eh?!

434
00:31:28,889 --> 00:31:31,889
Don't joke. That's not funny.

435
00:31:32,920 --> 00:31:36,445
- But what's your name?
- Eh?!

436
00:31:36,445 --> 00:31:40,447
Boss, are you saying you don't remember him?

437
00:31:40,447 --> 00:31:42,047
What?

438
00:31:46,057 --> 00:31:47,857
What's my name?

439
00:31:49,099 --> 00:31:51,949
Takegawa, obviously.

440
00:31:53,349 --> 00:31:54,641
And me?

441
00:31:54,641 --> 00:31:56,641
Maika Segawa.

442
00:31:56,641 --> 00:31:58,760
- Yes.
- Good, good.

443
00:31:58,765 --> 00:32:01,557
My surname is Kuribayashi, but what is my first name?

444
00:32:01,557 --> 00:32:03,157
Well...

445
00:32:04,641 --> 00:32:06,741
- Utamaro.
- That's a good one!

446
00:32:06,741 --> 00:32:08,248
What about me?

447
00:32:08,248 --> 00:32:10,857
- You're Justice.
- Justice!

448
00:32:12,149 --> 00:32:14,741
Stop, all of you! Quiet.

449
00:32:14,741 --> 00:32:17,349
Director, director, what about me? Me, me?

450
00:32:17,349 --> 00:32:19,482
What is your name?

451
00:32:19,482 --> 00:32:24,432
<i>Really? What is going on here?</i>

452
00:32:24,432 --> 00:32:26,708
<i>Why only me?</i>

453
00:32:26,708 --> 00:32:29,899
<i>Did he forget about me?</i>

454
00:32:31,140 --> 00:32:35,980
<i>After that, the Director tried really hard to remember me.</i>

455
00:32:41,682 --> 00:32:43,510
Thank you very much.

456
00:32:43,510 --> 00:32:45,050
<i>[Tenku Real Estate Co. Ltda.]</i>

457
00:32:51,682 --> 00:32:53,474
Let's go.

458
00:32:53,474 --> 00:32:55,732
- Excuse me.
- Watch out!

459
00:32:56,349 --> 00:32:57,990
Director.

460
00:32:59,170 --> 00:33:00,725
Director?

461
00:33:00,725 --> 00:33:02,325
Haru...?

462
00:33:03,840 --> 00:33:05,810
Yes, yes.

463
00:33:05,812 --> 00:33:07,312
Haru...

464
00:33:07,973 --> 00:33:08,808
<i>Haru-tan.</i>

465
00:33:08,808 --> 00:33:09,949
<i>Haru-tan.</i>

466
00:33:09,949 --> 00:33:11,432
You are Haruta.

467
00:33:11,432 --> 00:33:14,090
That was so close!

468
00:33:17,182 --> 00:33:19,082
Haruta.

469
00:33:22,599 --> 00:33:24,282
Shall we?

470
00:33:25,058 --> 00:33:30,099
<i>He still has trouble remembering our time together.</i>

471
00:33:30,099 --> 00:33:31,876
That was so close!

472
00:33:31,876 --> 00:33:33,642
<i>However...</i>

473
00:33:34,290 --> 00:33:36,510
Bibibibi.

474
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:41,310
Biiiiiiiii.

475
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:44,040
Biiiiiiiii.

476
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,790
<i>[Arakanan | Yudegoro]</i>

477
00:33:51,266 --> 00:33:54,475
I've told you repeatedly, that I'll never sell this place.

478
00:33:54,475 --> 00:33:56,892
Of course, we fully understand.

479
00:33:56,892 --> 00:33:59,567
But in order to build a city of smiles...

480
00:33:59,567 --> 00:34:01,683
Enough! Get out now!

481
00:34:01,683 --> 00:34:05,758
Actually, we have another favor to ask of you today.

482
00:34:10,308 --> 00:34:12,558
Chief, why are we doing this?

483
00:34:12,558 --> 00:34:15,453
If we know nothing about making udon noodles,

484
00:34:15,453 --> 00:34:21,892
how can we convince him to re-open his restaurant in our new development?

485
00:34:21,892 --> 00:34:23,600
That's a good tactic.

486
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:26,367
Haruta-san, you've got flour on you.

487
00:34:27,058 --> 00:34:29,433
Sorry, I'm making it worse.

488
00:34:29,433 --> 00:34:31,899
Then stop it.

489
00:34:34,808 --> 00:34:36,734
Don't get too close to him.

490
00:34:37,850 --> 00:34:42,033
Yes, but... I adore Haruta-san.

491
00:34:42,033 --> 00:34:44,601
- Haruta-san likes me too, right?
- Well, yes.

492
00:34:44,601 --> 00:34:46,693
That's a relief.

493
00:34:49,099 --> 00:34:50,350
Is that true?

494
00:34:50,350 --> 00:34:52,217
<i>What? Director?</i>

495
00:34:53,058 --> 00:34:56,516
I know. Why don't I move in with you?

496
00:34:56,516 --> 00:34:58,533
Why say that now?

497
00:34:58,533 --> 00:35:02,599
I heard from Maika that your housemate has moved out.

498
00:35:02,599 --> 00:35:04,825
Well, yes.

499
00:35:05,980 --> 00:35:07,890
Well, well...

500
00:35:09,099 --> 00:35:10,741
Is that true?

501
00:35:11,318 --> 00:35:13,405
Yes. <i> What?</i>

502
00:35:13,405 --> 00:35:17,034
<i>Don't tell me that he is in love with me again?</i>

503
00:35:17,601 --> 00:35:19,201
<i>Never!</i>

504
00:35:20,017 --> 00:35:22,726
Next time, let's play basketball on the video game together.

505
00:35:22,726 --> 00:35:25,818
- Sounds like fun.
- Yeah, it will be fun.

506
00:35:26,726 --> 00:35:28,326
Director, what are you doing?

507
00:35:28,326 --> 00:35:29,851
Don't hit him.

508
00:35:29,851 --> 00:35:32,292
I, Musashi Kurosawa,

509
00:35:32,292 --> 00:35:34,268
can play the game of Go.

510
00:35:34,809 --> 00:35:37,392
<i>What? This can't be true!</i>

511
00:35:37,392 --> 00:35:40,934
<i>No, it must be my imagination.</i>

512
00:35:40,934 --> 00:35:43,617
What's this?

513
00:35:44,476 --> 00:35:46,076
Let me see.

514
00:35:47,351 --> 00:35:50,434
I never thought I would see him smiling.

515
00:35:50,434 --> 00:35:52,793
He looks very happy.

516
00:35:58,684 --> 00:36:00,135
What's wrong, Justice?

517
00:36:00,135 --> 00:36:02,952
No, nothing at all.

518
00:36:05,020 --> 00:36:07,710
Watch out!

519
00:36:09,517 --> 00:36:11,217
Haruta!

520
00:36:12,642 --> 00:36:14,893
What the hell is going on?

521
00:36:14,893 --> 00:36:16,701
Bugger off!

522
00:36:18,225 --> 00:36:20,151
Please forgive us.

523
00:36:21,476 --> 00:36:25,218
Finish it before our next meeting next week.

524
00:36:33,309 --> 00:36:35,918
I'm almost finished.

